name: laura
about: Having given up cable about 3 years ago , and finishe law school at the same time, I now read a lot of books and magazines. My primary interest is fiction, but I love National Geographic and would be curious to read more books that capture the world the way it does. Devil's Teeth maybe was the closest I've come, or some Krackauer or Iyer books. I also read New York Review of Books and Gourmet. Biographies sometimes catch my eye. I lived in Italy for 3 years and like to read Italian novels too. Now I'm studying Spanish so will hopefully be able to leer un libro soon.

name: Mark Fullmer
about:
Born on the Planet Zantar 322 Earth-years ago. Superpowers include: breathing and talking simultaneously, long walks on the beach, and the ability to spell most words correctly.

I now live in Southern California, where I teach writing, occasionally make mistakes, and dream of PeaceCorpsing in some c'est la vie South American country.

I consider my happiest moment (so far) sitting on a cow-inhabited cliff in Zennor, Cornwall.

Have reduced my Twinkie habit to two packs a day.

I write intuitively, sing quietly, and love greasy pizza.

name: Beth
about: I have found that while I like a lot of the books I read, overall I would rate them as just ok. I feel like I am very stingy with my four and five star ratings. I have also finally realized that if I don't like a book, it's ok to stop reading. I have given up on a number of books (my DNF section), but I hope to revist some of them, in the hopes that my feelings change (which has happened before).
